cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about spiking neural networks with synaptic plasticity on a neuromorphic chip. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper evaluates the performance of the network on a set of tasks of varying complexity. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the computational properties of the network. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper talks about controlling the criticality of the network. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the relationship between criticality and task performance.
